The Catholic Church has appealed to the government to release the desks that were promised to various learning institutions in a bid to enhance social distancing when schools reopen in January.
Bishop Paul Kariuki, the chairman of the Catholic Commission for Education and Religious Education, said many institutions have not received the promised government assistance to help in the fight against the Covid-19 pandemic.



