He noted that some private school owners had been driven out of business due to harsh economic times, while others are struggling and some candidates could be inconvenienced.
“The government should know that there are no private students. Maybe there are mission (church owned) schools that need assistance. Private schools cannot be forced to stay in business if they do not have the capacity to operate.
“The government should work on how to help the private institutions since if they are closed, public schools could be overcrowded,” said Bishop Kariuki.
He at the same time urged parents to establish the status of the schools near them so as to know whether they are still in operation in order not to be shocked at the last minute.



