Buy enough face masks
He also appealed to the parents to ensure they buy enough face masks for their children and always monitor their progress so that if they need medication, they are attended to fast.
“Parents should buy their children at least four re-usable face masks. Schools boards of management should also ensure that the environment is conducive for learning and get isolation rooms in case students fall ill while in school. Parents should also bear the responsibility of taking care of their children who fall ill,” advised the bishop.
Bishop Kariuki also appealed to the TSC to replace teachers who have retired.

